      • attr

        public <E> Form<E> attr(Form<String> attr)

        Returns a function to access an attribute value in a test case. This can be used in SUITE, FIXTURE, and ORACLE stages.

        Type Parameters:
        E - Type of attribute value to be returned.
        Parameters:
        attr - Attribute name whose value should be returned

      • value

        public <E> Form<E> value(Form<String> entryName,
                         Form<?> target)

        Returns a function to invoke a method of a specified name. The returned value of the method will be returned as the function’s value.

        Type Parameters:
        E - Type of the function’s value to be returned.
        Parameters:
        entryName - A name of method to be invoked.
        target - A target from which value of entryName will be returned.
